    {
      "id": "b51a8bcca3f0aa3000e8d609756f0076e4ad72a5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-07-18 09:00:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: Code-Review+2\n\nI'm all for improving the test coverage of racer.\n\nLooking at the test results for racer under \"full\" testing it is actually looking in pretty good shape.  The question is whether we should enable the existing racer testing by default against all patches on lustre-review, and then land this patch after we fix any problems that arize with the addition of the new tests.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "ff177adb17143873e8741bd645ff38e135428ab8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2014-07-20 18:57:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nI am all for enabling racer testing by default.\n\nOn a different note - do we really need our own truncate binary in tests? Why not just drop it and use system-provided one at all times?\nI see it was added back in 2002 by Peter Braam with a great commit message of \"*** empty log message ***\".",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "53fa98b7f2f0f0f91a77c63f87ef1f9bc35e0dbc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-07-21 12:57:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nTruncate was only added to coreutils in 2008 (in or around version 7.0) so I guess that's why we have out own.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "7a77e2e8970d6caa988c0cc5cb4bdf9deac42fe7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2014-07-24 19:02:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nI wonder why no maloo checkmark still given that the tests have actually completed",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
